HEADWORD: Supercelestial
<hw>Su`per*ce*les"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>super-</ets> + <ets>celestial</ets>: cf. L.
<ets>supercaelestis</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Situated above the
firmament, or great vault of heaven.</def>
